uientry.unicode: PLACEHOLDER - The current level of growth.
Your tax modifies your income. It depends on your empire-wide tax level, technologies, your own or enemy characters in the province, and buildings.
The larger your empire grows, the more corruption you will encounter. It reduces your tax income. You can reduce corruption by researching certain civil technologies.

Exempting a region from tax can be useful when you have public order or food problems. ||When you exempt this province from tax, it will no longer produce income. In exchange, there is no negative public order effect from taxes in this province. Also, the province is removed from the food system: It no longer supplies or consumes food, as it is now self-sufficient.

state.unicode: Indifferent||The population are neither unhappy nor satisfied.
Unhappy||The population is troubled. Local growth and wealth may become affected.
Satisfied||The population is content. Local growth and wealth may improve if they are kept happy.
Indifferent||The population are neither unhappy nor satisfied.
Unhappy||The population is troubled. Local growth and wealth may become affected.
Satisfied||The population is content. Local growth and wealth may improve if they are kept happy.
Satisfaction||As public order rises the populace becomes increasingly motivated, thereby improving local growth and wealth.
Unrest||As public order drops the populace becomes increasingly agitated, thereby reducing local growth and wealth. When public order reaches -100 the province will experience an uprising.
